Key Match Events: Joey Veerman scored for the Netherlands in the 4th minute.
Maximilian Mittelstadt equalized for Germany in the 10th minute.
Niclas Fullkrug scored the winning goal for Germany with his shoulder in the 86th minute.
Post-Match Reflections: Jamal Musiala was the MVP, showing a wide range of skills and maturity.
Kai Havertz was an almost anonymous figure and was replaced in the 73rd minute.
Julian Nagelsmann's Germany will be a force to reckon with in Euro 2024 preparations.
Ronald Koeman will be disappointed with his team's finishing, having missed several chances.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Niclas Fullkrug scored his 11th international goal in just 15 appearances.
The match was held in Frankfurt.
